channel.title: How do I
channel.description:
How do i get rid of anti-leech?? i just want to try this server and play it a bit. i'm new to editing and just want to try to add objects and try to learn to code etc. This serve seems like it has a nice start and i'd like to play around with it -.- but i can't even get on b/c of anti-leech and i get loads of nulls =/
So please help me on how to get rid of it, don't give me some bs answer saying learn to code -.- b/c im trying -.-

item.title: How do I
item.dc:creator: @Owned_Pl0xs Owned_Pl0xs
item.description:
@Owned_Pl0xs wrote:

There is no specific anti-leech. Some known anti leeches I know of is making the playerId static or leaving in an extra bracket to give 100 errors.

Whatever the problem, you need to specify what problem you are getting and we might be able to help you out, but anti-leeches were made on purpose, so I think I will leave it to you to get to the core problem.

Good luck.
